sql:
SELECT device_name
FROM devices
WHERE status = 'inactive' AND location = 'Factory';

external_knowledge:
- "glowing with vitality" refers to the device being 'active';
- "the last to receive a visitor" means the device had the latest access date;
- "shimmering reflection of the latest timestamp" relates to the device status timestamp being the most recent;
- "stands as the beacon of activity" implies choosing the device with the highest activity based on the timestamp, limited to one result.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(param_value_id) AS total_parameters_above_threshold
FROM device_parameters
WHERE CAST(value AS REAL) > 1.0;
